cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.IT. 

This paper discusses a random sampling procedure on a graph and analyzes its performance measure. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also considers the use of this sampling procedure to find a target set of vertices, which relates to graph theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper derives exact and approximate expressions, which involves information theory (cs.IT).
